Commentary.Commentary: Back with action. Nijat Masood to bowl first. Andy Balbirnie and Peter Moor to open!
...Second innings.

Afghanistan didn't see it coming. They opted to bat first but wouldn't have imagined this kind of score. Only Ibrahim Zadran stood up for them, no one supported him! Afghanistan though lost him right after the Lunch break and if not for Janat's 41, they would have ended around 100. Still, not the start they would have liked to the game and now they have to bowl really well to keep Ireland under pressure. They have to be as consistent as Ireland were! Tea is taken as well. Join us back for the final session in a while.

An outstanding performance by the Irish team and they will be so happy right now. 10 wickets inside one and a half sessions and it was Mark Adair who made Afghanistan dance to his tunes. He was right on the money from the start. Bowled good lengths and lines and took two wickets in an over. Barry McCarthy and Craig Young supported him well too. Ireland after the lunch struck rightaway, removing Zadran and Rehman in quick succession. Curtis Campher followed it with two wickets in a row. However, Mark Adair was the pick with five wickets!
OUT! BOWLED! Through him! A length ball from around the wicket and on off. Khan fails to defend and it hits the top of off. Afghanistan end with 155!

LUNCH! Excellent start to the game! Ireland though will be the happy team right now. They were right on the money from the start. Mark Adair was very disciplined with his lines and lengths. He struck twice to put Afghanistan on the back foot but the hosts replied well with Zadran and Hashmatullah Shahidi playing some beautiful strokes and getting back on track. Both added around 50 runs before Hashmatullah Shahidi gave away his wicket down the leg side. Ibrahim Zadran though has held one end well with his fifty and will hope that Rahmanullah Gurbaz can glue with him to build a big stand. Ireland will hope their spinners get their lines right as they too are getting some purchase. Second session coming up shortly.

Commentary.Commentary: Time for the national anthems first. It will be of the Irish team first followed by of the Afghans. All set for action. Ibrahim Zadran and Noor Ali Zadran to open for Afghanistan. Mark Adair to bowl first. Let's play.
Ireland (PLAYING XI) - Peter Moor, Andy Balbirnie, Curtis Campher, Harry Tector, Paul Stirling (C), Lorcan Tucker (WK), Mark Adair, Andy McBrine, Barry McCarthy, Theo van Woerkom, Craig Young.

Afghanistan (PLAYING XI) - Ibrahim Zadran, Noor Ali Zadran, Rahmat Shah, Hashmatullah Shahidi (C), Nasir Jamal, Rahmanullah Gurbaz (WK), Karim Janat, Zia ur Rehman, Nijat Masood, Naveed Zadran, Zahir Khan.
TOSS - Afghanistan have won the toss and will BAT.

Ireland might be underdogs but they have a quality squad as well. A lot of familiar faces will be seen along with a couple of debutants. Andy Balbirnie will lead his side and the likes of Paul Stirling, Harry Tector and Mark Adair will bring their experience to it. Barry McCarthy or Matthew Foster could be in contention to make their debut for Ireland. Afghanistan might be favourites but do not sleep on Ireland who with this group can cause a lot of damage. Toss and team sheets next.

Hello and welcome to the action of Day 1 between Afghanistan and Ireland at Tolerance Oval. Afghanistan recently played a Test match against their Asian rivals, Sri Lanka but were beaten comprehensively by them. There were lots of positive though from the match. Ibrahim Zadran at the top, Shahidi's form but there were some concerns regarding their bowling group. However, Afghanistan are coming into his match with a couple of changes. Rahmanullah Gurbaz is in line to make his debut and so is Khalil Gurbaz.
...Day 1, Session 1...

Afghanistan will be happy with how they did in this session. Ireland at one time seemed like taking a lead of over 150 but Zia ur Rehman did well and finished with a fifer. Still a stiff task ahead, they need to bat well now and show more character and application. The Irish on the other hand, will love a similar performance to their first innings.

A good batting display from the Irish and they will feel they are in a good position in this game. They did not have anyone play a big innings but had a few decent partnerships which has helped them stretch their lead to over 100. Stirling was their highest scorer but the others contributed too with some decent scores. Overall, they'll be pleased with their effort.
OUT! TAKEN! That is the end of the innings. On middle. Andy looks to pull but gets a top edge on the leg side. It is taken by the fielder.

Commentary.Commentary: We are back!
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

Afghanistan began well but then it was hard work for their bowlers. The wicket isn't offering a lot and their bowlers had to toil hard. They were rewarded right towards the end and they'll hope this opens the floodgates. Will they dominate after the break? We will find out.

That wicket right at the end will give Afghanistan a lot of relief. Before that, this session was mostly about Ireland. They lost Tector early but Tucker and Stirling batted really well. They added around 80 and took their side into the lead. It seemed that Ireland would go into the break five down but Stirling fell right towards the end of the session. Ireland though will hope they can have a couple of such partnerships and push that lead over the 100 run mark.

OUT! TIMBER! Khan strikes right at the stroke of Lunch! Massive wicket as Stirling was looking good. This is tossed up on middle, it lands and spins back in. Stirling looks to defend but is beaten by the turn and this hits the stumps.

A fine show with the ball and then a decent start with the bat puts the Irish in ascendancy. They trail by just around 50 at the moment and have 6 wickets in hand. Harry Tector is well set and Striling has just walked out to the middle. They would hope these two can bat long and their first aim will be to get into the lead without losing anymore wickets. Afghanistan on the other hand, will hope to find early breakthroughs or they would fall welL behind in this game. An important first session awaits.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 ...

Ireland in reply lost their captain early on but Curtis Campher played brilliantly along with Harry Tector adding around 60 runs. Just at the stroke of stumps though Campher fell and the nightwatchmen, Theo van Woerkom too. Ireland still have a lot of batting left. For the hosts, Naveed Zadran and Zia ur Rehman bowled well but need more from others. Afghanistan will hope to pressurize Ireland in the first session on Day 2. Join us at 11.30 am IST (6 am GMT) and join us earlier for the build up. Till then, cheers!

An eventful day comes to end! Ireland will be happier of the two sides though. Afghanistan opted to bat first but were pushed on the back foot mainly by Mark Adair who was on top of his game. He bowled good lines and lengths and got two wickets in an over. Barry McCarthy and Craig Young supported him well too. Afghanistan tried to get back on track through Ibrahim Zadran but he too fell right after the Lunch break after his fifty. Karim Janat tried to show some fight but got no able support from the other end. Mark Adair was the pick as he ended with a five-for.

Commentary.Commentary: Ireland will be eager to chase this down. The bowlers have done the job and it is now upto the batters to finish it up. It was once again their seamers who did the job for them. Barry McCarthy, and Craig Young were exceptional. Right then! Just 111 runs to win. You expect Ireland to chase it down easily. Afghanistan though need to show some fight. Join us back for the chase in a while.

So, Afghanistan need 111 runs to win. The bowlers have done an incredible job in this match. Afghanistan had 7 wickets in hand at the start! Hashmatullah Shahidi though fell right at the start. His wicket opened the gates for Ireland who with their consistent lines and lengths got the rewards. Rahmanullah Gurbaz fell and the tail didn't add much as well. However, Naveed Zadran's knock helped Afghanistan get something to bowl at. Not a good performance by Afghanistan, they have really let themselves down with the bat.

LUNCH! An excellent session for Ireland and they should be really proud of how they've bowled. The seamers were bang on with their lines and lengths. In the first hour itself Ireland got two wickets of Hashmatullah Shahidi and Nasir Jamal. Rahmanullah Gurbaz and Karim Janat tried to get things back under control but fell too. Afghanistan are too defensive with their approach. How much can they soak the pressure too? Now Afghanistan have just three wickets to play with. The lead is of 74 runs but Ireland will hope to take the remaining wickets quickly in the next session and try to keep the hosts under 100. Stay tuned for the second session.

Hello and welcome to the action of Day 3. This match is moving at a fast pace and we feel whoever dominates Day 3 will have the upper hand in this game. Ireland though have done well so far to stay a foot ahead of their host. They batted well in the second innings and took a lead of more than 100 runs. However, Afghanistan gave a befitting reply by cutting out the trail in more than a session itself. Afghanistan lead right now by 26 runs. Hashmatullah Shahidi is well set on 53 while Rahmanullah Gurbaz is helping on his debut match as well. Afghanistan will hope to build this stand while Ireland will look to break it in the first hour. Stay tuned.
...Day 3, Session 1...

Ireland on the other hand, need the others to contribute as well. Adair has two out of the three to fall and has by far been their best bowler again. He really needs the others to contribute and give him able support. The wicket seems to be flattening out but if you hit the right lines and lengths, there is something in it for the bowlers. Day 3 is an important one. Do join us for it. Till then, goodbye and take care.

It is the skipper who is leading the fight back after they lost two early wickets. Noor supported him well and now Gurbaz has started well. They'll dearly hope these two can bat long and take them to a safer position. Still three days to go so they can take their time.
Afghanistan have fought back well so far! Their batting display has been a lot better than their first innings but there is still a long way to go as Ireland still are ahead in this game.
A dot and that will be Stumps! On middle, blocked.

Commentary.Commentary: That's it from this game, a day to remember for the Irish as they bag their first Test win. They'll be hoping it is just the start. Afghanistan on the other hand, have a lot to improve. They haven't had the best of times in this format in recent times. We hope you enjoyed our company. Until next time, goodbye and take care.

Andy Balbirnie says he is very happy. They were really good through out. Adds they bowled really well and with a lot of discipline. Mentions they just needed one partnership chasing a small score and they got it. Also says he is proud of the boys and it is a big achievement. Ends by saying he hopes to improve from here on and do well in the limited opportunities.

Hashmatullah Shahidi says they let themselves down with the bat in the first innings. Adds the Irish bowled really well. Adds they did have a few positives, Gurbaz and Naveed were good and credits Zia for the way he bowled. Ends by congratulating the Irish for their first win.

Mark Adair, Man of the Match, says he is feeling great and he is enjoying the moment. States the boys were brilliant and they are extremely happy. Adds Test cricket was difficult but he hopes they can kick on from here. Mentions the players have been excellent and it was superb performance. Ends by saying he is looking forward for the shorter format.

Chasing a small target, they did lose four wickets early but Tucker and Balbirnie played brilliantly. They added over 50. Balbirnie scored a fine half-ton and Tucker supported him well to create history for Ireland.

It was Ireland's pacers yet again who shined the second time around. They yet again bowled out Afghanistan for a moderate total. Young, Barry and Adair all ended with three wickets each and ensured they did not have to chase a big score.

In reply, a combined batting effort saw them take a lead of around 100. Stirling was the star with the bat with a half-ton but there were a few more who got to decent scores which helped them get that lead.

History has been created! This is Ireland's first-ever Test win and it is a convincing one in the end. Right from Day 1 they have dominated. First, they bowled Afghanistan for a low score thanks to a fifer from Adair.
There are the winning runs! Fuller and on the pads. Tucker looks to flick but gets an inside edge. It rolls on the leg side for one. Ireland win by 6 wickets.

Commentary.Commentary: We are back for what could be the last session of the day and possibly of the match too! Stirling and Balbirine walk out to resume their innings. Zia ur Rehman to begin.
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

Afghanistan have fought back well! Ireland still in the driving seat but credit to the character shown by the hosts. They are defending a small total but got three wickets early. Stirling and Balbirnie though have steadied the ship a little. The Irish would hope these two can continue the good work. Afghanistan on the other hand, will know if they get these two, game could well and truly be in their side. Join us for what could be the last session of this game in a bit.
